// Content Sprint 4: Commercials, Tax and Marketplace Finance.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_4 = {"commercial-model":{"summary":"Choose how your marketplace earns revenue from each Seller, who controls the customer selling price and how Marketplacer calculates the amount owed to the Seller. Marketplacer supports commission and wholesale commercial models, and different Sellers can use different models within the same marketplace.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Commercial","Finance","Seller management","Marketplace operations","Legal and tax","Technology"],"sections":{"Understanding the Commercial Model":"<p>Your commercial model defines the financial relationship between you and each Seller. It determines how you earn revenue, who controls customer pricing, which product values must be supplied to Marketplacer and how the Seller amount is calculated.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Operator earnings</th><th>Typical price owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Commission</td><td>A percentage of eligible sales</td><td>Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale or cost-plus</td><td>The difference between customer selling price and agreed wholesale cost</td><td>Operator</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The model is configured for each Seller, allowing commission and wholesale Sellers to operate in the same marketplace.</p><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Keep the commercial and operating models separate.</strong> Commission or wholesale controls pricing and remittance calculations. It does not by itself decide inventory ownership, fulfilment, merchant of record, customer support, returns or chargeback responsibility.</div><h3>Confirm before live Seller onboarding</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Commercial model and effective date</li><li>Customer price owner</li><li>Promotion funding</li><li>Postage treatment</li><li>Tax treatment</li><li>Refund and chargeback responsibility</li><li>Remittance delay and payout process</li><li>Product and Order integration requirements</li></ul>","Commission Model":"<p>Under a commission model, the Seller generally supplies the product, stock and selling price. Marketplacer applies the Seller's assigned Commission Package and deducts the resulting commission from the eligible sale value.</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Commission Packages</code></p><p>Assign the approved package under:</p><p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Commission Package Details</code></p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer item price</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Commission rate</td><td>20%</td></tr><tr><td>Operator commission</td><td>$20</td></tr><tr><td>Starting Seller amount</td><td>$80</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The simplified example excludes postage, tax, Merchant Fees, promotions and refunds.</p><h3>Use commission when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The Seller owns retail pricing</li><li>Commercial terms can be expressed as a percentage</li><li>Seller systems update prices frequently</li><li>Category, Brand or price-tier rules provide sufficient flexibility</li><li>The marketplace expects a scalable Seller population</li></ul><h3>Confirm the complete commission basis</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Default and custom rates</li><li>Commission on line-item postage</li><li>Commission tax</li><li>Promotion funding</li><li>Merchant Fees</li><li>Refund treatment</li><li>Future package changes</li></ul>","Wholesale Model":"<p>Under a wholesale model, the Seller provides an agreed cost for each Variant and the Operator controls or approves the customer selling price. Marketplacer uses the Wholesale Price as the starting amount owed to the Seller.</p><p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Wholesale Preferences</code></p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer item price</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale Price</td><td>$75</td></tr><tr><td>Operator gross margin</td><td>$25</td></tr><tr><td>Starting Seller amount</td><td>$75</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Wholesale pricing is maintained at Variant level, so cost can differ by size, colour, pack or other configuration.</p><h3>Use wholesale when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The supplier provides product-level costs</li><li>The Operator controls customer pricing</li><li>Margin must be managed by product or Variant</li><li>The Operator owns the promotional calendar</li><li>The marketplace has the pricing capability to maintain retail values at scale</li></ul><h3>Protect wholesale data</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Restrict access to cost fields and exports</li><li>Define the source of truth</li><li>Approve permanent and promotional cost changes</li><li>Monitor minimum margin</li><li>Retain supplier price approvals</li></ul>","Mixed Commercial Models":"<p>A single marketplace can support commission Sellers, wholesale Sellers and Seller groups with different Commission Packages. Record the model against every Seller and make it visible to commercial, operations and Finance teams.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller</th><th>Model</th><th>Operator earnings</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller A</td><td>Commission</td><td>15% of eligible sales</td></tr><tr><td>Seller B</td><td>Commission</td><td>Category-based Commission Package</td></tr><tr><td>Supplier C</td><td>Wholesale</td><td>Customer price less Variant Wholesale Price</td></tr><tr><td>Supplier D</td><td>Wholesale</td><td>Product-specific margin</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Where one commercial relationship contains several arrangements, assess whether it can be represented through Category rates, Brand rates, price tiers, Variant-level wholesale costs or separate Seller accounts.</p><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Keep the design understandable.</strong> A simpler Commission Package or consistent Seller model is easier to test, reconcile and explain than an unnecessarily fragmented structure.</div>","Comparing Responsibilities and Control":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Decision area</th><th>Commission</th><th>Wholesale</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer selling price</td><td>Usually maintained by the Seller</td><td>Controlled or approved by the Operator</td></tr><tr><td>Operator earnings</td><td>Percentage commission</td><td>Margin between customer price and wholesale cost</td></tr><tr><td>Seller amount</td><td>Sale value less commission and adjustments</td><td>Wholesale Price and adjustments</td></tr><tr><td>Pricing maintenance</td><td>Primarily Seller-owned</td><td>Primarily Operator-owned</td></tr><tr><td>Promotions</td><td>Requires agreed funding rules</td><td>Requires margin and supplier-cost review</td></tr><tr><td>Scalability</td><td>Usually simpler for large Seller populations</td><td>Requires stronger pricing operations</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Define promotion funding</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller-funded</li><li>Operator-funded</li><li>Shared funding</li><li>Temporary commission reduction</li><li>Temporary wholesale cost reduction</li></ul><p>For every promotion, record the original price, promotional price, funding split, calculation basis, tax treatment and Seller remittance impact.</p><h3>Define fulfilment and customer responsibility separately</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Dispatch SLA</li><li>Shipping and tracking</li><li>Cancellation and return ownership</li><li>Warranty</li><li>Customer support</li><li>Invoice and refund responsibility</li></ul>","Financial Flow and Remittance":"<h3>Commission flow</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Customer sale value recorded</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Commission and applicable charges calculated</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Refunds and tax treatment applied</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Net Seller amount becomes eligible for Remittance</strong></div></div><h3>Wholesale flow</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Wholesale Price recorded for each Variant</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Eligible quantity and postage evaluated</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Fees, refunds and tax treatment applied</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Net Seller amount becomes eligible for Remittance</strong></div></div><p>Remittance calculation and payout are separate. The Seller Invoice must satisfy fulfilment, approval, delay, schedule and positive-balance checks before the amount is processed for payment.</p><h3>Finance must reconcile</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Customer payment</li><li>Order and Seller Invoices</li><li>Commission or Wholesale Price</li><li>Merchant Fees and tax</li><li>Refunds and adjustments</li><li>Remittance Advice</li><li>Completed payout</li></ul>","Choosing the Model":"<h3>Commercial questions</h3><ol><li>How should the Operator earn revenue?</li><li>Who controls retail pricing?</li><li>Is the agreement percentage-based or cost-based?</li><li>Does the commercial value vary by product?</li><li>Who funds promotions?</li><li>How are postage, Merchant Fees, tax, refunds and chargebacks treated?</li><li>What are the Remittance terms?</li></ol><h3>Operational questions</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Who creates and maintains products?</li><li>How often do prices or costs change?</li><li>Who approves changes and investigates pricing errors?</li><li>Who owns post-launch commercial audits?</li></ul><h3>Technology questions</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Source of truth for customer price</li><li>Source of truth for Wholesale Price</li><li>Promotion synchronisation</li><li>Protection of Operator-controlled values</li><li>Failed-update monitoring</li><li>End-to-end Sandbox testing</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Obtain appropriate legal, accounting and tax advice.</strong> Marketplacer configuration should implement the approved commercial model rather than determine it.</div>","Recording and Implementing the Decision":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Register field</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller</td><td>Example Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Commercial model</td><td>Commission</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Package or wholesale basis</td><td>Homewares 15%</td></tr><tr><td>Postage and Merchant Fee treatment</td><td>Recorded</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion funding</td><td>Shared by written approval</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance delay</td><td>14 days</td></tr><tr><td>Tax position</td><td>Finance approved</td></tr><tr><td>Sandbox test</td><td>Passed</td></tr><tr><td>Production status</td><td>Applied</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Implementation sequence</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Confirm the signed agreement</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Configure the Seller and commercial settings in Sandbox</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Create representative products and Variants</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Test Orders, promotions, refunds and Remittances</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Reconcile with Finance</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Apply the approved Production setup</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Validate the first live transactions</strong></div></div><h3>Approval checklist</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller agreement matches the model</li><li>Price and cost ownership confirmed</li><li>Promotion funding confirmed</li><li>Tax and fees reviewed</li><li>Refund and Remittance terms confirmed</li><li>Integration requirements tested</li><li>Finance reconciliation complete</li><li>Ongoing owner assigned</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360057263531-Set-up-your-commission-packages\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Set up your commission packages</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115006597508-Manage-seller-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage seller accounts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["wholesale-configuration","Wholesale Configuration"],["commercial-financial-decisions","Commercial and Financial Decisions"]]},"commission-packages":{"summary":"Create reusable commission structures, assign them to Sellers and control how commission varies by Category, Brand, product price and line-item postage. Test each package before activation and schedule future package changes where required.","audience":["Commercial","Marketplace operations","Seller management","Finance","Tax","Technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Commission Packages":"<p>Commission Packages define how much commission you earn from eligible Seller sales. Each package contains a name, Default Rate, optional commission on line-item postage and optional custom rates by Category, Brand or Category price point.</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Commission Packages</code></p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Package</th><th>Default rate</th><th>Example use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard</td><td>20%</td><td>General Seller base</td></tr><tr><td>Strategic Partner</td><td>15%</td><td>Negotiated Sellers</td></tr><tr><td>Beauty</td><td>20%</td><td>Category and Brand exceptions</td></tr><tr><td>Launch</td><td>10%</td><td>Temporary introductory terms</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Marketplacer evaluates custom rules from top to bottom and applies the first match. The Default Rate applies when no custom rule matches.</p><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Rule order changes the result.</strong> Place the most specific commercial exception above broader Category rules and test products that match more than one condition.</div>","Enabling Commission Packages":"<p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Commission Settings</code></p><p>Review:</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Enable commission packages</li><li>Enable commission calculation based on commission packages</li><li>Exclude line item postage commission from refunds</li></ul><p>Use this controlled sequence when moving from legacy Commission Rules:</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Document the existing structure</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Enable Commission Packages</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Create and test packages</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Assign every Seller</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Enable package-based calculation at the approved time</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Validate new Orders</strong></div></div><p>Commission is captured when the Order is submitted. Test changes using new Orders rather than expecting historic financial records to recalculate.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Restrict commission permissions.</strong> Only authorised commercial, marketplace operations or Finance users should create, edit, delete, assign or schedule Commission Packages.</div>","Planning Your Package Structure":"<p>Design packages from signed Seller agreements and the approved commercial framework.</p><h3>Begin with the standard position</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Marketplace Default Rate</li><li>Commission on postage</li><li>Category and Brand exceptions</li><li>Price thresholds</li><li>Temporary rates and effective dates</li><li>Tax and refund treatment</li><li>Sellers covered by each package</li></ul><h3>Use reusable packages</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Create one package for shared terms</li><li>Use clear names that describe the arrangement</li><li>Create Seller-specific packages only for genuinely unique terms</li><li>Avoid test or ambiguous package names in Production</li></ul><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Package</th><th>Default</th><th>Custom rules</th><th>Postage</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard</td><td>20%</td><td>None</td><td>No</td></tr><tr><td>Beauty</td><td>20%</td><td>Skincare 15%, Fragrance 18%</td><td>No</td></tr><tr><td>Premium Brands</td><td>22%</td><td>Brand A 15%, Brand B 17%</td><td>Yes</td></tr><tr><td>Electronics</td><td>18%</td><td>Over $1,000 at 10%</td><td>Yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Custom rates depend on accurate Category and Brand data. Include commercial impact in catalogue governance and mapping reviews.</p>","Creating and Managing Packages":"<h3>Create a package</h3><ol><li>Open Configuration &gt; Commission Packages.</li><li>Select Create package.</li><li>Enter the Package Name and Default Rate.</li><li>Decide whether commission applies to line-item postage.</li><li>Add approved custom rates.</li><li>Review rule order and save.</li><li>Create a Sandbox Order to verify the result.</li></ol><p>The starting default package may contain a 5% rate. Update it to your approved marketplace default before live Seller onboarding.</p><h3>Edit, duplicate or delete</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Treat edits to an active shared package as financial changes</li><li>Use duplication when a new agreement is similar but not identical</li><li>Review inherited rules and postage settings after duplication</li><li>Before deletion, identify assigned Sellers and select the approved replacement</li></ul><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Register field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Package name and Default Rate</td><td>Identifies the arrangement</td></tr><tr><td>Custom rules and order</td><td>Documents the calculation</td></tr><tr><td>Commission on postage</td><td>Records shipping treatment</td></tr><tr><td>Assigned Sellers</td><td>Shows commercial scope</td></tr><tr><td>Effective date and approval</td><td>Supports change control</td></tr><tr><td>Sandbox and Production status</td><td>Supports verification</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Custom Rates and Rule Priority":"<p>Add custom rates by Category or Brand. Category rules can also include a secondary rate above a price threshold.</p><h3>Example rule order</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Rule</th><th>Rate</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>Brand A</td><td>12%</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>Skincare Category</td><td>15%</td></tr><tr><td>Fallback</td><td>Default Rate</td><td>20%</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A Brand A product in Skincare receives 12% because the Brand rule is evaluated first. Rates are not combined.</p><h3>Price-point example</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Electronics product price</th><th>Applied rate</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>$500</td><td>15% base Category rate</td></tr><tr><td>$1,000</td><td>15% base Category rate</td></tr><tr><td>$1,000.01</td><td>10% secondary rate</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Test values below, exactly at and immediately above each threshold. Also test promotional prices, tax model, quantities and partial refunds.</p><h3>Classification controls</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Approved Category level</li><li>Canonical Brand record</li><li>Duplicate Brand prevention</li><li>Mapping review</li><li>Impact assessment before Category restructuring</li></ul>","Commission on Postage and Refunds":"<p>Enable <strong>Apply commission on line item postage</strong> within a package where the Seller agreement includes postage in the commission basis.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Item price</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Line-item postage</td><td>$10</td></tr><tr><td>Applicable rate</td><td>20%</td></tr><tr><td>Item commission</td><td>$20</td></tr><tr><td>Postage commission</td><td>$2</td></tr><tr><td>Total commission</td><td>$22</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A marketplace-wide control is also available:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings &gt; Charge commission on line item postage for all orders</code></p><p>Use package-level settings for differentiated agreements or the global control for one consistent policy. Document which control governs the marketplace.</p><h3>Refund treatment</h3><p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Commission Settings &gt; Exclude line item postage commission from refunds</code></p><p>When enabled, the Operator retains the postage commission while the related item commission is reversed according to the completed Refund Request. Test the exact result in Sandbox.</p>","Assigning and Scheduling Packages":"<h3>Assign one Seller</h3><p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Commission Package Details</code></p><p>Select the approved package and update the account. Verify the Seller, agreement, effective date, postage treatment, Merchant Fees and Remittance terms before saving.</p><h3>Assign in bulk</h3><ol><li>Open Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers.</li><li>Select Import Sellers and download the template.</li><li>Enter the exact package name in the Commission Package column.</li><li>Upload the file and review results.</li><li>Check representative Seller accounts.</li></ol><h3>Schedule a future change</h3><p><code>Configuration &gt; Commission Package Scheduling</code></p><p>Use scheduling for contract renewals, end of an introductory rate or another future effective date. Record the Seller ID, current package, future package, activation date and approvals.</p>","Testing and Ongoing Governance":"<h3>Minimum package test</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Default Rate product</li><li>Every Category rule</li><li>Every Brand rule</li><li>Product matching Brand and Category</li><li>Below, at and above each threshold</li><li>Line-item postage</li><li>Promotional price</li><li>Multiple quantities</li><li>Multi-Seller Order</li><li>Cancellation and full or partial refund</li></ul><h3>Verify</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Applied rate and amount</li><li>Commission tax</li><li>Postage commission</li><li>Seller amount</li><li>Refund adjustment</li><li>Remittance impact</li><li>Commission Invoice where enabled</li></ul><h3>Investigate discrepancies in this order</h3><ol><li>Package assigned when the Order was submitted</li><li>Package-based calculation setting</li><li>Default Rate</li><li>Custom-rule order</li><li>Product Category and Brand</li><li>Price relative to threshold</li><li>Postage setting</li><li>Promotion, tax and refund activity</li></ol><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Prefer a new package for material future changes.</strong> Creating a new package and scheduling its assignment can be clearer than editing a shared package that already applies to several Sellers.</div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360057263531-Set-up-your-commission-packages\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Set up your commission packages</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/19909387582477-Assign-commission-packages-to-sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Assign commission packages to sellers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/9202254142477-Commission-on-shipping\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Commission on shipping</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38122804710029-Managing-Commission-on-Postage-and-Refunds\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Managing Commission on Postage and Refunds</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["commercial-model","Choosing the Commercial Model"],["merchant-fees","Merchant Fees and Charges"],["seller-account-creation","Seller Account Creation"]]},"wholesale-configuration":{"summary":"Enable wholesale functionality for an approved Seller, capture the agreed wholesale cost for each Variant and maintain the customer selling price separately. Test margin, mixed pricing, refunds and Remittance calculations before publishing live wholesale products.","audience":["Commercial","Marketplace operations","Pricing and merchandising","Finance","Catalogue","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Wholesale Configuration":"\n<p>Wholesale uses the agreed Variant-level Wholesale Price as the starting amount owed to the Seller rather than calculating commission on the customer selling price.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Wholesale is configured on each Variant.</strong> Every applicable Variant must have <strong>Variant is wholesale</strong> selected and a positive Wholesale Price. A Seller can contain both commission and wholesale Variants.</div>\n<p>The customer selling price, Wholesale Price, RRP and any wholesale promotional cost serve different purposes. Confirm who owns each field and how it reaches Marketplacer.</p>\n","Enabling Wholesale for a Seller":"<p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Wholesale Preferences</code></p><h3>Review the available controls</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Display wholesale fields, reporting only</td><td>Shows Wholesale Price and RRP fields without activating wholesale Remittance calculation</td></tr><tr><td>Enable wholesale functionality for sellers</td><td>Allows Variants to use the wholesale pricing model</td></tr><tr><td>Display wholesale promotional fields, reporting only</td><td>Shows temporary wholesale promotion fields and dates</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Before enabling</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Signed wholesale agreement</li><li>Wholesale-price source</li><li>Customer-price owner</li><li>Tax and postage treatment</li><li>Promotion and refund responsibility</li><li>Remittance terms</li><li>Integration assessment</li><li>Pricing access controls</li></ul><p>For an existing catalogue, identify every Variant that will change model, populate its approved Wholesale Price, review customer pricing and validate a controlled group before wider Production changes.</p>","Wholesale Pricing and Margin":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer selling price</td><td>Amount charged to the customer</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale Price</td><td>Starting amount owed to the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Recommended Retail Price</td><td>Reference price for pricing and merchandising</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale Promo Price</td><td>Temporary supplier cost during an approved campaign</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Margin</h3><p><code>Effective customer selling price - Effective Wholesale Price = Gross product margin</code></p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Customer price</th><th>Wholesale cost</th><th>Gross margin</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard</td><td>$100</td><td>$75</td><td>$25</td></tr><tr><td>Operator-funded sale</td><td>$90</td><td>$75</td><td>$15</td></tr><tr><td>Supplier-supported sale</td><td>$90</td><td>$68</td><td>$22</td></tr><tr><td>Cost increase not reflected in retail</td><td>$100</td><td>$82</td><td>$18</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use the tax-inclusive or tax-exclusive convention configured for the environment. Finance should define whether internal reporting uses margin percentage or markup and document the formula.</p><h3>Controls</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Minimum-margin threshold</li><li>Cost effective date</li><li>Retail-price approval</li><li>Promotion funding</li><li>Access to commercially sensitive fields</li><li>First Order review after any cost change</li></ul>","Maintaining Wholesale Prices":"\n<p>Choose one source of truth for wholesale status and Wholesale Price, then define which people or systems may change them.</p>\n<h3>Manual Seller Portal update</h3>\n<p>Open <code>Seller Portal &gt; Products &gt; Manage Products &gt; Edit product &gt; Edit Variant</code>.</p>\n<ol><li>Select <strong>Variant is wholesale</strong>.</li><li>Enter a positive <strong>Wholesale Price</strong>.</li><li>Enter RRP where required.</li><li>Review the customer selling price and margin.</li><li>Save the Variant.</li></ol>\n<h3>Bulk update</h3>\n<p>Open <code>Seller Portal &gt; Products &gt; Bulk Manage Products &gt; Manage product information</code> and include the relevant Wholesale columns.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Pricing Model</li><li>Wholesale Price or Variant Wholesale Price</li><li>Recommended Retail Price or Variant Recommended Retail Price</li><li>Advert ID and Variant ID</li></ul>\n<p>Set every applicable Variant to the wholesale pricing model and enter the approved cost. Upload the workbook through <strong>Manage product information</strong> and review representative Variants afterwards.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Entering Wholesale Price alone does not activate wholesale.</strong> Omitting the pricing model can leave the Variant on commission treatment.</div>\n","Promotions and Price Changes":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Funding model</th><th>Customer price</th><th>Wholesale cost</th><th>Gross margin</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Normal</td><td>$100</td><td>$75</td><td>$25</td></tr><tr><td>Operator-funded promotion</td><td>$90</td><td>$75</td><td>$15</td></tr><tr><td>Supplier-funded promotion</td><td>$90</td><td>$65</td><td>$25</td></tr><tr><td>Shared promotion</td><td>$90</td><td>$70</td><td>$20</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Where supported, use Wholesale Promo Price together with both promotion start and end dates. Coordinate the customer sale price, supplier cost, time zone, funding owner, margin and refund treatment.</p><h3>Permanent cost-change process</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Receive the approved supplier file</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Match affected Variants</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Calculate margin using current customer prices</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Approve required retail changes</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Apply cost and price updates through their source systems</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Verify representative products</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Review the first affected Orders</strong></div></div><p>A later Wholesale Price edit does not retroactively recalculate existing Orders. Validate changes with a new Order.</p>","Integrations and Order Creation":"<h3>Define the source of truth for</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Pricing model</li><li>Wholesale Price</li><li>RRP</li><li>Customer Base Price and Sale Price</li><li>Wholesale promotional cost and dates</li><li>Tax</li><li>Stock</li><li>SKU and external IDs</li></ul><p>Protect Operator-controlled customer prices from unintended Seller-feed overwrites. Test initial creation, stock-only updates, cost changes, promotions, remapping and integration reconnection.</p><h3>Mixed pricing from the same Seller</h3><p>A Seller can have Marketplace-priced and Wholesale-priced Variants. When an <code>orderCreate</code> request contains both models for the same Seller, Marketplacer separates them into two Seller Invoices:</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller Invoice</th><th>Contains</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace-priced Invoice</td><td>Line Items calculated using the assigned Commission Package</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale-priced Invoice</td><td>Line Items calculated using Wholesale Price</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Test checkout totals, Invoice splitting, fulfilment, refunds and reporting so operational teams understand why one Seller can receive two Invoices from the same customer Order.</p><h3>Monitor failures</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Missing Wholesale Price</li><li>Invalid pricing model</li><li>Cost above customer price</li><li>Failed product update</li><li>Failed Order creation</li><li>Promotion-date errors</li><li>Stale supplier cost file</li></ul>","Testing Wholesale Orders and Refunds":"<h3>Minimum test catalogue</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>One Variant</li><li>Several Variants with different costs</li><li>Standard and sale price</li><li>Wholesale promotional cost</li><li>Postage</li><li>Multiple quantities</li><li>Marketplace-priced comparison product</li><li>Order containing both pricing models for one Seller</li></ul><h3>Verify each Order</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Customer total</li><li>Seller Invoice split</li><li>Line Item pricing model</li><li>Wholesale amount</li><li>Commission where applicable</li><li>Tax and postage</li><li>Operator margin</li><li>Remittance eligibility</li><li>Reporting output</li></ul><h3>Refund scenarios</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Pre-dispatch cancellation</li><li>Full return</li><li>Partial quantity</li><li>Postage refund</li><li>Returnless refund</li><li>Refund before Remittance</li><li>Refund after payout</li></ul><p>For the first live wholesale Seller, review the Seller settings, cost file, representative Variants, first successful Order, resulting Seller Invoices and first Remittance before scaling the catalogue.</p>","Ongoing Pricing Governance":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Responsibility</th><th>Suggested owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Supplier cost agreement</td><td>Commercial</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale-price maintenance</td><td>Marketplace operations or pricing</td></tr><tr><td>Customer selling price</td><td>Merchandising or ecommerce</td></tr><tr><td>Margin approval</td><td>Commercial and Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Integration</td><td>Technology</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion funding</td><td>Commercial and marketing</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance reconciliation</td><td>Finance</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Regular exception monitoring</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Cost above selling price</li><li>Margin below threshold</li><li>Missing Wholesale Price</li><li>Expired wholesale promotion</li><li>Customer promotion without supplier support</li><li>Unexpected pricing model</li><li>Difference from supplier source</li><li>First Orders after a cost change</li></ul><h3>Supplier-price audit</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Receive current price list</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Match by SKU or approved identifier</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Compare with Marketplacer</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Calculate margin impact</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Approve and apply changes</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Review import results and affected Orders</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Retain reconciliation evidence</strong></div></div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115006597508-Manage-seller-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage seller accounts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39486165269645-Bulk-product-management-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk product management overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580919800077-How-to-manage-products-and-variants-in-bulk-single-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage products and variants in bulk, single sheet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/6555008333069-Schedule-price-promotions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Schedule price promotions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://dev.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_wholesale_order/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wholesale Orders</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["commercial-model","Choosing the Commercial Model"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["source-of-truth-planning","Source-of-Truth Planning"]]},"merchant-fees":{"summary":"Decide whether payment-processing costs should be absorbed by the marketplace or recovered from Sellers. Configure default merchant fees, apply approved Seller or payment-method exceptions and test how each fee affects Seller Invoices, refunds and Remittances.","audience":["Commercial","Finance","Marketplace operations","Seller management","Tax","Payments","Technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Merchant Fees and Charges":"<p>A Merchant Fee deducts an agreed payment-processing charge from the amount remitted to a Seller. It can recover gateway, card-processing or other approved transaction costs.</p><p>The fee affects the Operator and Seller financial calculation. It does not increase the product price displayed to the customer.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Charge</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Commission</td><td>Operator revenue from a commission Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale margin</td><td>Customer price less Wholesale Price</td></tr><tr><td>Merchant Fee</td><td>Recovery of agreed payment-processing cost</td></tr><tr><td>MPay payout-processing fee</td><td>Cost of processing a Seller payout</td></tr><tr><td>Additional Charge</td><td>Separate customer Invoice after the original Order</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A Seller can have both commission or wholesale calculation and a Merchant Fee. Define each component in the Seller agreement.</p>","Deciding What to Charge":"<p>Review the marketplace's actual payment costs, including percentage and fixed gateway fees, alternative payment methods, currency costs, refund fees and chargebacks.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Approach</th><th>Base</th><th>Percentage</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Operator absorbs cost</td><td>$0.00</td><td>0%</td></tr><tr><td>Percentage only</td><td>$0.00</td><td>1.5%</td></tr><tr><td>Fixed only</td><td>$0.50</td><td>0%</td></tr><tr><td>Fixed plus percentage</td><td>$0.50</td><td>1.0%</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A fixed fee has a larger proportional effect on low-value Seller Invoices. A multi-Seller Order can create several Seller Invoices, so the fixed component can apply more than once across the customer Order.</p><h3>Confirm</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Cost-recovery position</li><li>Fixed and percentage components</li><li>Postage in the calculation basis</li><li>Tax</li><li>Seller exceptions</li><li>Payment-method exceptions</li><li>Refund treatment</li><li>Effective date and Seller disclosure</li></ul>","Configuring the Default Merchant Fee":"<p><code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings &gt; Subscriptions and Charges</code></p><p>Configure:</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Merchant Fee Base</li><li>Merchant Fee Percentage</li></ul><p>The standard calculation is:</p><p><code>(Order value x Merchant Fee Percentage) + Merchant Fee Base = Total Merchant Fee</code></p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Item value</td><td>$90</td></tr><tr><td>Postage</td><td>$10</td></tr><tr><td>Calculation value</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Percentage at 1%</td><td>$1.00</td></tr><tr><td>Base fee</td><td>$0.50</td></tr><tr><td>Total Merchant Fee</td><td>$1.50</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>After saving, create a new Sandbox Order and verify each Seller Invoice, postage basis, Merchant Fee tax and Remittance result.</p>","Seller and Payment-Method Overrides":"<h3>Seller-specific values</h3><p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Custom Merchant Fees</code></p><p>Leave a field blank to inherit the marketplace default. Enter the approved value, including zero where the agreement requires no charge for that component.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Configuration</th><th>Base</th><th>Percentage</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace default</td><td>$0.50</td><td>1.5%</td></tr><tr><td>Strategic Seller</td><td>$0.00</td><td>1.0%</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Payment-method values</h3><p><code>Configuration &gt; Payment Methods</code></p><p>Configure provider-specific Merchant Fees where processing costs differ by gateway. Test each enabled payment method and any overlap with Seller-specific values.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller</th><th>Payment method</th><th>Expected result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard Seller</td><td>Standard gateway</td><td>Default or gateway-approved fee</td></tr><tr><td>Strategic Seller</td><td>Standard gateway</td><td>Approved Seller override</td></tr><tr><td>Standard Seller</td><td>Premium gateway</td><td>Approved gateway fee</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Calculating the Merchant Fee":"<h3>Commission Seller example</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Order value</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Commission</td><td>$9.00</td></tr><tr><td>Merchant Fee</td><td>$1.50</td></tr><tr><td>Starting Seller Remittance</td><td>$89.50</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>This example assumes commission is applied to a $90 item, postage is passed to the Seller and commission does not apply to postage.</p><h3>Multi-Seller example</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller Invoice</th><th>Fixed fee</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller A</td><td>$0.50</td></tr><tr><td>Seller B</td><td>$0.50</td></tr><tr><td>Seller C</td><td>$0.50</td></tr><tr><td>Total across customer Order</td><td>$1.50</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Reconciliation</h3><p><code>Customer Order value - commission or wholesale adjustment - Merchant Fee - refunds and withheld tax = Seller Remittance</code></p><p>Finance should be able to trace the fee and its tax to the relevant Seller Invoice and payout.</p>","Tax and Financial Documents":"<p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Tax Settings &gt; Merchant Fee tax rate (%)</code></p><p>Confirm whether Merchant Fees are taxable, the applicable rate, whole-percentage entry, tax-inclusive or tax-exclusive treatment and required Seller documents.</p><h3>Commission Invoice</h3><p>Where enabled, the Commission Invoice can show commission, Merchant Fees and related tax. Sellers can access it through the Seller Portal Order actions.</p><p>Review the Seller-level <strong>Hide commission invoice</strong> setting only where an approved alternative document process provides the required information.</p><h3>Retain</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Approved fee schedule</li><li>Tax advice</li><li>Seller agreement</li><li>Sandbox Invoice and refund examples</li><li>Remittance Advice</li><li>Production verification</li></ul>","Refunds and Remittance Adjustments":"<p>Define whether the fixed, percentage or full Merchant Fee is returned to the Seller when an Order is cancelled or refunded.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Possible policy</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller stock cancellation</td><td>Seller carries approved processing cost</td></tr><tr><td>Operator error</td><td>Operator absorbs the fee</td></tr><tr><td>Customer change of mind</td><td>Seller agreement applies</td></tr><tr><td>Damaged product</td><td>Seller-funded treatment</td></tr><tr><td>Partial refund</td><td>Approved proportional or fixed treatment</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>During Refund Request finalisation, review the customer refund, Line Item adjustment, commission, Merchant Fee, postage, tax and any amount already remitted.</p><p>A refund after Seller payout can create an amount to reclaim through later Remittances. Monitor negative Seller positions and resolve balances before Seller closure.</p>","Other Marketplace Charges and Ongoing Governance":"<h3>Keep other charges distinct</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Charge</th><th>Who is charged</th><th>Where it appears</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Merchant Fee</td><td>Seller</td><td>Deducted from Remittance</td></tr><tr><td>MPay payout-processing fee</td><td>Seller or Operator according to setup</td><td>MPay Remittance reporting</td></tr><tr><td>Additional Charge</td><td>Customer</td><td>Separate Invoice linked to the original Order</td></tr><tr><td>Refund adjustment</td><td>Seller or Operator according to policy</td><td>Refund and Remittance records</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Additional Charges Invoices require the applicable advanced amendment and Finance settings and should not be confused with Merchant Fees.</p><h3>Minimum testing</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Single and multi-Seller Orders</li><li>Postage</li><li>Low and high value</li><li>Default and Seller override</li><li>Each payment method</li><li>Commission and wholesale Sellers</li><li>Full and partial refunds</li><li>Remittance reconciliation</li></ul><h3>Change control</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Identify affected Sellers</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Review agreements and tax</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Test new values in Sandbox</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Approve effective date</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Apply Production change</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Validate first new Orders</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Retain evidence</strong></div></div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360055605531-Setting-Merchant-Fees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Setting Merchant Fees</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038673291-Calculating-remittance-on-orders\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Calculating remittance on orders</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/37709603707405-Additional-charges-invoices-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Additional charges invoices overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/45368727546637-Remittance-reporting-with-MPay-automated-payouts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Remittance reporting with MPay</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["tax","Tax"],["additional-charges","Additional Charges"]]},"promotions-campaign-management":{"summary":"Configure and govern marketplace Promotions, decide who funds each customer discount, manage Operator-created and Seller-created campaigns, prevent pricing conflicts, submit accurate Promotion adjustments and reconcile customer, Seller and Operator outcomes.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Commercial","Marketing","Finance","Seller management","Customer service","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understand Marketplacer Promotions":"\n<p>A Marketplacer Promotion applies a discount or customer benefit when the configured conditions are satisfied. Promotions can be created by the marketplace Operator or an authorised Seller.</p>\n<p>Operators access Promotions through:</p><p><code>Marketing &gt; Promotions</code></p>\n<p>The Promotions Dashboard allows authorised users to view Active, Upcoming and Expired Promotions, create campaigns, edit them, suspend them and delete them.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Campaign objective</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Action and eligibility configured</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Customer receives the benefit</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Funding affects Seller remittance</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Campaign is reconciled</strong></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>A Promotion is not only a marketing activity.</strong> It is also a pricing, Seller-funding, remittance, integration and Finance event.</div>\n<p>Before creating a Promotion, confirm what the customer receives, which Sellers and products qualify, who funds the benefit, how the storefront applies it, how the Seller is paid, how refunds are handled and how success will be measured.</p>\n","Choose the Right Discount Mechanism":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Capability</th><th>Marketplacer Promotion</th><th>Scheduled Sale Price</th><th>Coupon Code</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer action</td><td>Applied when conditions are met</td><td>Customer sees a temporary lower price</td><td>Customer supplies a code</td></tr><tr><td>Representation</td><td>Separate Promotion adjustment</td><td>Product or Variant price</td><td>Depends on storefront implementation</td></tr><tr><td>Targeting</td><td>Seller, Brand, Category, product, Variant, spend and loyalty</td><td>Specific product or Variant</td><td>Defined by coupon platform</td></tr><tr><td>Funding split</td><td>Supports Operator and Seller funding</td><td>Usually represented through product price</td><td>Must be mapped into the Order model</td></tr><tr><td>Typical use</td><td>Campaigns and conditional offers</td><td>Simple temporary markdown</td><td>Targeted or customer-entered offer</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Use a Marketplacer Promotion when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Several Sellers or products participate</li><li>The campaign uses spend thresholds, loyalty or conditional eligibility</li><li>The offer provides free shipping, a bonus item or buy-one-get-one-free</li><li>The Operator funds some or all of the discount</li><li>The discount should appear separately in the Order</li></ul>\n<h3>Use a scheduled Sale price when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>One product or Variant needs a temporary lower price</li><li>No broader eligibility logic is required</li><li>The product source supports the scheduled fields</li><li>The temporary price should be the selling price</li></ul>\n<p>Scheduled Sale price fields are separate from Marketplacer Promotions and are not synchronised through some MConnect product-source flows. Confirm source ownership before relying on them.</p>\n<h3>Use a coupon code when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The storefront owns coupon redemption</li><li>The customer must enter a code</li><li>The integration can submit the correct Marketplacer financial adjustment</li></ul>\n","Plan the Campaign":"\n<h3>Define the objective</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Increase conversion or average Order value</li><li>Support a Seller launch</li><li>Clear ageing stock</li><li>Increase Category awareness</li><li>Encourage product trial or loyalty engagement</li><li>Reduce shipping-cost resistance</li><li>Support a seasonal or marketplace-wide campaign</li></ul>\n<h3>Define scope and eligibility</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Participating Sellers, Categories and Brands</li><li>Included and excluded products or Variants</li><li>Minimum or maximum spend</li><li>Loyalty or geographic scope</li><li>Start and end dates</li><li>Sale-price eligibility</li></ul>\n<h3>Define the commercial position</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Total customer discount</li><li>Operator-funded and Seller-funded amounts</li><li>Commission and Merchant Fee treatment</li><li>Shipping and tax treatment</li><li>Refund treatment</li><li>Approved campaign budget</li></ul>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Activity</th><th>Recommended owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Campaign objective</td><td>Commercial or Marketing</td></tr><tr><td>Seller participation</td><td>Seller management</td></tr><tr><td>Funding approval</td><td>Finance and Commercial</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion configuration</td><td>Authorised Operator user</td></tr><tr><td>Storefront implementation</td><td>Ecommerce or Technology</td></tr><tr><td>Financial reconciliation</td><td>Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Campaign reporting</td><td>Commercial or Analytics</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Retain an approved campaign brief containing the objective, Promotion ID, eligible Sellers and products, customer offer, funding split, budget, dates, test evidence, measures, owners and approvers.</p>\n","Create an Operator Promotion":"\n<p>Go to <code>Marketing &gt; Promotions</code>, then:</p><ol><li>Select <strong>New Promotion</strong>.</li><li>Enter the Promotion details.</li><li>Configure at least one action.</li><li>Add eligibility filters where required.</li><li>Review funding.</li><li>Validate the date range.</li><li>Save or schedule the Promotion.</li><li>Test it before customer launch.</li></ol>\n<p>A Promotion requires at least one action. Filters alone do not create a working Promotion.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Name</td><td>Customer-readable discount line and reporting identifier</td></tr><tr><td>Start Date and End Date</td><td>Campaign schedule</td></tr><tr><td>Teaser and URL</td><td>Optional customer-facing campaign message and destination</td></tr><tr><td>Description</td><td>Internal context</td></tr><tr><td>Suspend Promotion</td><td>Temporarily disables new use</td></tr><tr><td>Cost Borne by Marketplace</td><td>Operator-funded share of the discount</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Naming standard</h3><p>Use a short, customer-readable and unique name that can also be understood in Orders, Invoices and reports.</p>\n<pre><code>Winter Marketplace Sale 2026</code></pre>\n","Configure Promotion Actions":"\n<p>At least one action must be configured.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Fixed amount discount</td><td>$10 off</td></tr><tr><td>Percentage discount</td><td>20% off</td></tr><tr><td>Discount for every nominated spend</td><td>$5 off for every $50 spent</td></tr><tr><td>Fixed price per unit</td><td>Eligible items reduced to $20 each</td></tr><tr><td>Free shipping</td><td>Domestic, or domestic and international</td></tr><tr><td>Bonus item</td><td>Add a nominated free product</td></tr><tr><td>Buy one, get one free</td><td>Add another unit of the applicable Variant</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>A bonus item that requires a size, colour or other customer selection can create an ambiguous outcome. Choose a product and Variant structure that the storefront can apply predictably.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Campaign objective</th><th>Possible action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Increase conversion</td><td>Fixed or percentage discount</td></tr><tr><td>Increase basket value</td><td>Spend-based discount</td></tr><tr><td>Clear stock</td><td>Fixed price or percentage discount</td></tr><tr><td>Reduce delivery friction</td><td>Free shipping</td></tr><tr><td>Encourage product trial</td><td>Bonus item</td></tr><tr><td>Increase units per Order</td><td>Buy one, get one free</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Configure Eligibility and Filters":"\n<p>Filters determine which customers, products and Orders qualify.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Minimum and maximum spend</li><li>Included and excluded Brands</li><li>Included and excluded Categories</li><li>Included and excluded products</li><li>Included and excluded Variants</li><li>Loyalty-program eligibility</li><li>Linked Promotion conditions</li><li>Exclusion of Sale-priced products</li></ul>\n<p>When a filter is enabled, include at least one valid value. Empty enabled filters can prevent the Promotion from being saved or applied correctly.</p>\n<h3>Target the narrowest accurate level</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use Seller scope when every eligible product from one Seller participates</li><li>Use Category scope for a Category campaign</li><li>Use product scope when all relevant Variants qualify</li><li>Use Variant scope when only selected sizes, colours or configurations qualify</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not target both a parent product and its individual Variants in the same Promotion.</strong></div>\n<h3>Test broad scope</h3><p>A Promotion with no limiting filters may apply broadly across the Seller or marketplace. Test at least one intentionally ineligible product before activation.</p>\n","Understand Cost Borne by Marketplace":"\n<p><strong>Cost Borne by Marketplace</strong> determines how much of the customer discount is funded by the Operator. The remaining amount is funded by the Seller through the remittance position.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cost Borne by Marketplace</th><th>Operator funds</th><th>Seller funds</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0%</td><td>0%</td><td>100%</td></tr><tr><td>25%</td><td>25%</td><td>75%</td></tr><tr><td>50%</td><td>50%</td><td>50%</td></tr><tr><td>75%</td><td>75%</td><td>25%</td></tr><tr><td>100%</td><td>100%</td><td>0%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Seller-funded</h3><pre><code>Customer discount:             $20\nCost Borne by Marketplace:      0%\nOperator contribution:          $0\nSeller-funded discount:        $20</code></pre>\n<h3>Operator-funded</h3><pre><code>Customer discount:             $20\nCost Borne by Marketplace:    100%\nOperator contribution:         $20\nSeller-funded discount:         $0</code></pre>\n<h3>Shared funding</h3><pre><code>Customer discount:             $20\nCost Borne by Marketplace:     50%\nOperator contribution:         $10\nSeller-funded discount:        $10</code></pre>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>The customer receives the same benefit regardless of the funding split. The funding decision changes the financial outcome between the Operator and Seller.</strong></div>\n","Calculate Promotion Funding and Remittance":"\n<p>Assume an original product price of $100, a $20 customer discount and no tax, commission or fees in the first example.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Marketplace share</th><th>Operator funds</th><th>Seller funds</th><th>Seller gross position</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0%</td><td>$0</td><td>$20</td><td>$80</td></tr><tr><td>25%</td><td>$5</td><td>$15</td><td>$85</td></tr><tr><td>50%</td><td>$10</td><td>$10</td><td>$90</td></tr><tr><td>75%</td><td>$15</td><td>$5</td><td>$95</td></tr><tr><td>100%</td><td>$20</td><td>$0</td><td>$100</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<pre><code>Seller gross position\n=\nCustomer amount\n+\nOperator-funded Promotion contribution</code></pre>\n<h3>Add commission and Merchant Fees</h3><p>Assume the transaction contains $10 commission and a $2 Merchant Fee. Use the actual Invoice values rather than calculating historical fees independently.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Marketplace share</th><th>Seller gross</th><th>Commission</th><th>Merchant Fee</th><th>Simplified remittance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0%</td><td>$80</td><td>-$10</td><td>-$2</td><td>$68</td></tr><tr><td>25%</td><td>$85</td><td>-$10</td><td>-$2</td><td>$73</td></tr><tr><td>50%</td><td>$90</td><td>-$10</td><td>-$2</td><td>$78</td></tr><tr><td>75%</td><td>$95</td><td>-$10</td><td>-$2</td><td>$83</td></tr><tr><td>100%</td><td>$100</td><td>-$10</td><td>-$2</td><td>$88</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>The actual result may also include tax, postage, commission on postage, withheld tax, refunds and other adjustments.</p>\n<h3>API representation</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><code>amountCents</code> is the full customer discount and is negative</li><li><code>amountToWithholdFromSellerRemittanceCents</code> is the Seller-funded portion and is positive</li><li><code>sourceId</code> identifies the Marketplacer Promotion</li><li><code>description</code> supplies the human-readable adjustment label</li></ul>\n<pre><code>Customer discount:                         $20\nSeller-funded portion:                      $5\nOperator-funded portion:                   $15\n\namountCents:                              -2000\namountToWithholdFromSellerRemittanceCents: 500</code></pre>\n","Govern Seller-Created Promotions":"\n<p>Sellers can create Promotions only after the Operator enables <strong>Marketing Tools access</strong>.</p>\n<p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Account Access</code></p>\n<p>The Seller can then access <code>Marketing &gt; Promotions</code> in the Seller Portal.</p>\n<h3>Enabling access is a governance decision</h3><p>Marketing Tools can affect customer pricing, Seller earnings, the campaign calendar, storefront display, remittance, refunds and marketplace reputation.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Governance question</th><th>Required decision</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Can the Seller create campaigns independently?</td><td>Yes, no or limited</td></tr><tr><td>Must the Seller notify the Operator?</td><td>Notice period</td></tr><tr><td>Is approval required?</td><td>Approval owner and process</td></tr><tr><td>Who funds the campaign?</td><td>Seller, Operator or shared</td></tr><tr><td>Can campaigns overlap?</td><td>Validation and calendar rules</td></tr><tr><td>Who checks customer display?</td><td>Marketing or Operations</td></tr><tr><td>How are results reported?</td><td>Required campaign measures</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Recommended process</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Seller submits campaign brief</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Operator reviews timing and funding</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Seller creates a suspended Promotion</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Campaign is tested and activated</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Operator monitors customer and Finance outcomes</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>Where no platform approval gate exists, use an external campaign calendar and approval process.</p>\n","Configure Promotion Validation":"\n<p>Go to:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Promotion Settings</code></p>\n<p>Available controls can block:</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Unvetted Adverts</li><li>Unpublished Adverts</li><li>Unvetted Variants</li><li>Unpublished Variants</li><li>Overlapping Promotion date ranges</li><li>Overlapping Sale-price date ranges</li></ul>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Benefit</th><th>Consideration</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Block unvetted products</td><td>Prevents unapproved products entering campaigns</td><td>Can block launch campaigns awaiting vetting</td></tr><tr><td>Block unpublished products</td><td>Prevents offline products being selected</td><td>Products must be published before configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Block Promotion overlaps</td><td>Reduces double-discount risk</td><td>Broad filters can create unexpected conflicts</td></tr><tr><td>Block Sale-price overlaps</td><td>Protects pricing rules</td><td>Can affect Order creation while conflicts remain</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Define whether the marketplace permits campaigns on products awaiting vetting, scheduled campaigns before publication, several Promotions on one product or Promotions on Sale-priced Variants.</p>\n","Manage Overlaps and Conflicts":"\n<p>Overlap detection can be triggered by a matching Brand, Category, product or Variant. The complete filter sets do not need to be identical.</p>\n<h3>Example</h3><pre><code>Promotion A\nCategory: Shoes\nBrand: Brand X\n\nPromotion B\nCategory: Shoes\nSeller: Seller A</code></pre>\n<p>These may conflict because both include the same Category.</p>\n<h3>Sale-price conflict</h3><p>When Sale-price overlap prevention is enabled, an Order can fail if the same Variant is included in a Promotion and an overlapping Sale-price schedule. Review active and upcoming Promotions, Sale-price dates and affected Variants before enabling the control.</p>\n<h3>Maintain a Promotion calendar</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Promotion name and ID</li><li>Seller and Category</li><li>Start and end date</li><li>Funding split</li><li>Sale-price overlap</li><li>Storefront assets</li><li>Approval status</li></ul>\n","Integrate Promotions with the Storefront":"\n<p>In a Connected marketplace, Marketplacer stores Promotion information, while the storefront and integration layer implement the customer experience.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Marketplacer stores Promotion configuration</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Storefront evaluates eligibility</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Cart applies the benefit</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Payment captures the discounted amount</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>orderCreate submits the Promotion adjustment</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>The Operator API can expose Promotion ID, Seller, name, dates, spend limits, suspension state, discount action, free shipping and included or excluded Brands, Categories, products and Variants.</p>\n<h3>Order adjustment requirements</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><code>adjustmentType: PROMOTION</code></li><li>Negative <code>amountCents</code></li><li>Positive Seller-remittance withholding</li><li>Customer-readable description</li><li>Promotion ID as <code>sourceId</code></li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Promotion adjustments are applied to Line Item inputs.</strong> Do not submit one broad Invoice-level discount and expect Marketplacer to allocate it across Sellers.</div>\n<h3>Multi-Seller basket</h3><pre><code>Customer Order\n├── Seller A Invoice\n│   ├── Eligible promoted Line Item\n│   └── Ineligible Line Item\n└── Seller B Invoice\n    └── Eligible promoted Line Item</code></pre>\n<h3>Prevent duplicate discounts</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm the customer benefit is applied once</li><li>Confirm eligible Line Items and the Promotion ID</li><li>Confirm customer, Seller-funded and Operator-funded amounts</li><li>Confirm Sale-price treatment</li><li>Confirm the final customer payment</li></ul>\n","Understand Orders, Invoices and Refunds":"\n<p>Promotion details can appear in the cart, customer Order confirmation, buyer Invoice, remittance records and Line Items reporting. Reconcile the customer discount at Line Item level.</p>\n<h3>Cancellation and refund principles</h3><ol><li>Start from the amount actually paid by the customer.</li><li>Review the original Promotion adjustment.</li><li>Confirm the Seller-funded and Operator-funded shares.</li><li>Review original commission and fees.</li><li>Avoid refunding more than the customer paid.</li><li>Confirm the Invoice Amendment and remittance recovery.</li><li>Reconcile the payment refund.</li></ol>\n<h3>Full refund example</h3><pre><code>Original product price:         $100\nCustomer Promotion discount:    -$20\nCustomer paid:                   $80</code></pre>\n<p>The customer should not ordinarily receive a $100 cash refund for that Line Item when they paid $80. The Seller and Operator funding adjustments must be handled separately so the contribution is not recovered twice.</p>\n<h3>Partial refund</h3><p>Review the Promotion allocation at the affected Line Item and quantity. Do not divide a spend-threshold, bonus-item or buy-one-get-one-free offer without an approved policy.</p>\n<h3>Bonus and BOGO returns</h3><p>Define whether the free item must be returned, what happens when the paid item is returned, whether eligibility is lost, which Seller bears the cost and how the storefront and Marketplacer record the outcome.</p>\n","Report and Reconcile Promotion Performance":"\n<p>Promotion reporting must distinguish customer benefit, Seller funding, Operator funding, Sales, commission, Merchant Fees, refunds, remittance and campaign cost.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Measure</th><th>Question answered</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Promotion Orders and units</td><td>How much activity used the Promotion?</td></tr><tr><td>Gross product value</td><td>What was the original product value?</td></tr><tr><td>Customer discount and paid value</td><td>What did customers save and pay?</td></tr><tr><td>Operator-funded amount</td><td>What did the marketplace fund?</td></tr><tr><td>Seller-funded amount</td><td>What was borne through Seller remittance?</td></tr><tr><td>Commission and Merchant Fees</td><td>What platform revenue was generated?</td></tr><tr><td>Refund value</td><td>What promoted value was later reversed?</td></tr><tr><td>Net promoted Sales</td><td>What remains after approved refund treatment?</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Promotion configuration</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Storefront discount and customer payment</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Marketplacer Line Item adjustment</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Seller Invoice and remittance</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Refunds and Invoice Amendments</strong></div></div></div>\n<h3>Campaign cost</h3><pre><code>Operator campaign cost\n=\nOperator-funded Promotion amounts\n+\nother approved marketing costs\n-\nrecovered or reversed amounts</code></pre>\n<p>Do not report the full customer discount as Operator cost when Sellers funded part of the Promotion.</p>\n","Operate and Close Campaigns":"\n<h3>Before launch</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Configuration and funding approved</li><li>Eligible products published and stocked</li><li>Overlap checks completed</li><li>Storefront assets ready</li><li>Eligible and ineligible carts tested</li><li>Sellers and Customer service briefed</li><li>Finance calculation tested</li></ul>\n<h3>During campaign</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Monitor customer pricing and eligibility</li><li>Monitor stock and Seller questions</li><li>Monitor Order creation and integration errors</li><li>Monitor funding values, complaints and budget</li></ul>\n<h3>Suspend rather than delete during investigation</h3><p>Use <strong>Suspend Promotion</strong> when pricing is wrong, scope is too broad, the campaign must pause, the budget is exhausted or an integration defect appears. Suspension preserves the record while stopping new use.</p>\n<h3>Campaign closure</h3><ol><li>Confirm the Promotion expired or was suspended.</li><li>Remove storefront banners and campaign content.</li><li>Confirm no new Orders receive the benefit.</li><li>Reconcile Promotion Orders and late refunds.</li><li>Confirm Seller remittance and campaign cost.</li><li>Compare results with the objective.</li><li>Retain evidence and lessons.</li></ol>\n","Troubleshoot Promotion Issues":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Issue</th><th>Review</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Promotion does not apply</td><td>Dates, suspension, action, filters, spend, IDs, Sale exclusion, loyalty and storefront eligibility</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion applies too broadly</td><td>Missing filters, exclusions, product versus Variant targeting and marketplace-wide scope</td></tr><tr><td>Wrong Seller funding</td><td>Cost Borne by Marketplace, customer amount, Seller withholding, Line Item and remittance</td></tr><tr><td>Order creation fails</td><td>Stock, publication, Promotion and Sale-price overlap, sourceId and adjustment values</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion not visible in records</td><td>Description, sourceId, Line Item adjustment, confirmation and Invoice display</td></tr><tr><td>Seller created an unexpected Promotion</td><td>Marketing Tools access, approval policy, calendar, funding and storefront publication</td></tr><tr><td>Expired Promotion remains advertised</td><td>CMS schedule, cache, banner dates, campaign URL and integration refresh</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Suspend the Promotion when customer, Seller or financial risk remains unresolved.</p>\n","Promotion Permissions and Change Control":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Permission area</th><th>Typical access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Manage promotions</td><td>Create, update and delete marketplace Promotions</td></tr><tr><td>Create and manage Sellers</td><td>Edit approved Seller access settings</td></tr><tr><td>Manage marketplace configuration</td><td>Access Promotion Settings</td></tr><tr><td>GraphQL API and API keys</td><td>Query Promotions and submit connected Order adjustments</td></tr><tr><td>View Orders and remittances</td><td>Review transaction and funding outcomes</td></tr><tr><td>View Activity Logs</td><td>Review user and system changes</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Apply least privilege</h3><p>Separate permission to design the campaign, approve funding, configure or activate the Promotion, change Seller access, modify the storefront and reconcile Finance.</p>\n<h3>High-risk changes</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Marketplace-wide Promotions</li><li>Fully Operator-funded campaigns</li><li>Campaigns with no limiting filters</li><li>Free international shipping</li><li>Overlapping periods</li><li>Seller Marketing Tools access</li><li>Changes after customer advertising begins</li><li>Emergency manual financial adjustments</li></ul>\n","Test Promotions End to End":"\n<h3>Actions and filters</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Fixed amount, percentage, spend-based and fixed-price discounts</li><li>Domestic and international free shipping</li><li>Bonus item and buy-one-get-one-free</li><li>Minimum and maximum spend</li><li>Included and excluded Seller, Brand, Category, product and Variant</li><li>Loyalty and Sale-item exclusion</li></ul>\n<h3>Funding and Finance</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>0%, 25%, 50%, 75% and 100% Cost Borne by Marketplace</li><li>Commission, Merchant Fees, postage and tax</li><li>Seller remittance</li><li>Full and partial cancellation or return</li><li>Bonus-item and BOGO return policy</li></ul>\n<h3>Seller-created Promotions</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Marketing Tools disabled and enabled</li><li>Seller creates a suspended Promotion</li><li>Operator visibility and campaign approval</li><li>Storefront synchronisation</li></ul>\n<h3>Validation and integration</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Unvetted and unpublished Products or Variants</li><li>Overlapping Promotions and Sale prices</li><li>Eligible, ineligible and multi-Seller carts</li><li>Correct sourceId, customer amount and Seller withholding</li><li>Duplicate prevention and failed orderCreate</li></ul>\n<h3>Records</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Customer Order display and buyer Invoice</li><li>Line Items report</li><li>Seller Invoice and Remittance Advice</li><li>Refund and Invoice Amendment reconciliation</li></ul>\n","Operator Readiness Checklist":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Promotions have one named business owner</li><li>Operator permissions are restricted</li><li>Seller Marketing Tools access has an approval process</li><li>Seller-created Promotion rules are documented</li><li>Campaign objectives and measures are agreed</li><li>Promotions, Sale prices and coupon codes are distinguished</li><li>Actions, filters and broad-scope risks are understood</li><li>Cost Borne by Marketplace is understood</li><li>Seller-funded, Operator-funded and shared campaigns are tested</li><li>Commission, Merchant Fee, postage and tax treatment are approved</li><li>Refund and cancellation treatment is documented</li><li>Validation and overlap settings are tested</li><li>The connected storefront can query and apply Promotions</li><li>orderCreate adjustments are correct at Line Item level</li><li>Duplicate-discount controls are in place</li><li>Customer, Seller and Operator records reconcile</li><li>Campaign budget and live monitoring have owners</li><li>Suspension and closure procedures are documented</li><li>Raw reporting evidence is retained</li><li>Every live campaign has an approved brief and test record</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38152011701133-Accessing-and-creating-Promotions-in-the-Operator-portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Accessing and Creating Promotions in the Operator Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38151977084557-Configuring-Promotions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configuring Promotions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/40586060515597-How-to-create-a-promotion-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Create a Promotion in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38229196692877-Promotion-validation-rules-and-settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Promotion Validation Rules and Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/38152064507277-Promotion-display-in-orders-and-invoices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Promotion Display in Orders and Invoices</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/7748531266189-Promotions-via-the-GraphQL-API\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Promotions via the GraphQL API</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/6555008333069-Schedule-price-promotions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Schedule Price Promotions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator User Role Permissions</a></li></ul>\n"},"related":[["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["merchant-fees","Merchant Fees and Charges"],["remittances","Remittances"],["refund-financial-adjustments","Refund Financial Adjustments"],["finance-reporting-operations","Finance Reporting"]]},"tax":{"summary":"Configure how Marketplacer calculates tax on items, postage, Merchant Fees and commission. Establish default rates, control Category and product exceptions, decide whether tax is withheld from Seller Remittances and test the complete Order, refund and reporting flow.","audience":["Finance","Tax","Marketplace operations","Commercial","Seller management","Catalogue","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Tax in Marketplacer":"<p>Marketplacer records tax against individual financial components, including items, postage, commission, Merchant Fees, refunds and Additional Charges Invoices.</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Tax Settings</code></p><p>Your organisation must approve the legal and accounting position, including who collects and remits tax, Seller registration requirements, standard and exceptional product rates, documents and refund treatment.</p><p>Tax values are selected when the Order is submitted. Later configuration or product changes apply to new Orders and do not recalculate existing transactions.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Marketplacer implements the approved tax model.</strong> Obtain appropriate tax and accounting advice for the jurisdictions in which the marketplace operates.</div>","Confirming the Platform Tax Model":"<p>Each environment is created as tax-inclusive or tax-exclusive. Confirm this foundational model with Marketplacer before Seller onboarding, product feeds, checkout and Order integration design.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Price entered</th><th>Tax result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Tax-inclusive</td><td>$110 at 10%</td><td>Pre-tax value $100, tax component $10, customer price $110</td></tr><tr><td>Tax-exclusive</td><td>$100 at 10%</td><td>Tax $10 added, customer total $110</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Confirm alignment across</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Production and Sandbox</li><li>Customer-price source</li><li>Ecommerce checkout</li><li>Payment gateway</li><li>Order payload</li><li>Seller Invoice</li><li>Refunds and reporting</li></ul><p>A mismatch between platform model and supplied values can produce incorrect customer totals, tax and Remittance calculations.</p>","Configuring Default Tax Settings":"<p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Tax Settings</code></p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Item tax rate (%)</td><td>Marketplace-wide item default</td></tr><tr><td>Postage tax rate (%)</td><td>Tax on Line Item postage</td></tr><tr><td>Merchant Fee tax rate (%)</td><td>Tax on Merchant Fees</td></tr><tr><td>Commission tax rate (%)</td><td>Tax on commission</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Enter whole percentage values:</p><p><code>10 = 10%, 5 = 5%, 0 = 0%</code></p><p>The Platform Default Rate remains the final fallback where no more specific rate exists.</p><h3>After a change</h3><ol><li>Record the approval and effective date.</li><li>Save the settings.</li><li>Review Reporting &gt; Audit Logs.</li><li>Create a new Sandbox Order.</li><li>Verify item, postage, commission and Merchant Fee tax.</li><li>Complete a Refund Request and reconcile the Remittance.</li></ol>","Tax Rate Hierarchy":"<p>Marketplacer uses the most specific populated item rate:</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Variant Tax Rate</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Advert Tax Rate</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Category Tax Rate</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Item Tax Rate</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Platform Default Rate</strong></div></div><p>Blank means inherit the next available rate. Zero means apply a genuine 0% rate.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Variant value</th><th>Result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Blank</td><td>Continue to Advert, Category or default</td></tr><tr><td>0</td><td>Apply 0%</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>Apply 5%</td></tr><tr><td>10</td><td>Apply 10%</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Where rates exist at several Category levels, the most granular applicable Category is used unless an Advert or Variant rate overrides it.</p><p>The hierarchy is evaluated for every Line Item, allowing one Order to contain different tax treatments.</p>","Category, Advert and Variant Tax Rates":"<h3>Category override</h3><p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories &gt; Edit Category &gt; Override Sales Tax</code></p><p>Use a Category rate when an approved product group differs from the marketplace default. Apply it at the correct Category depth and assess recategorisation impact.</p><h3>Advert rate</h3><p>Use the Advert item tax rate where every Variant in an Advert shares the same exception.</p><h3>Variant rate</h3><p>Use the Variant item tax rate where one Variant differs from the others. It has the highest priority.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Recommended level</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Most products share one rate</td><td>Item tax rate</td></tr><tr><td>Entire Category differs</td><td>Category override</td></tr><tr><td>One product differs</td><td>Advert rate</td></tr><tr><td>One Variant differs</td><td>Variant rate</td></tr><tr><td>External tax service classifies products</td><td>Tax code</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Product-tax fields are not standard Product Vetting triggers, so use spreadsheet validation, integration controls and tax reporting audits.</p>","Seller Tax Registration and Tax Codes":"<h3>Seller registration</h3><p>Collect the Seller's legal entity, registration number, tax status, jurisdiction, effective date and supporting evidence during onboarding. Record the Seller's declaration rather than providing legal advice.</p><p>Where enabled, Sellers can review registration status under:</p><p><code>Seller Portal &gt; Account Settings &gt; Store Information</code></p><h3>Tax codes</h3><p>A tax rate is a percentage. A tax code is a classification used by an external tax service. Marketplacer uses the most granular available code from Variant, Product or Category.</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Tax Settings &gt; Enable tax code validation</code></p><p>Before enabling validation, load the approved code list, review existing Category and product values, update Seller instructions and test accepted and rejected codes.</p>","Withholding Tax From Seller Remittances":"<p><code>Configuration &gt; Finance Settings &gt; Tax Settings</code></p><p>Review:</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Withhold item tax from being remitted to Sellers</li><li>Withhold postage tax from being remitted to Sellers</li></ul><p>When disabled, applicable tax is included in the Seller Remittance. When enabled, the tax is deducted from the Seller position and retained by the Operator.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Tax-inclusive example</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer item total</td><td>$110</td></tr><tr><td>Pre-tax value</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Item tax</td><td>$10</td></tr><tr><td>Seller starting amount when passed through</td><td>$110</td></tr><tr><td>Seller starting amount before other deductions when withheld</td><td>$100</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Withholding is captured when the Order is created. A later setting change applies only to new Orders. Marketplacer withholding does not itself file or remit tax to an authority.</p>","Testing, Reporting and Governance":"<h3>Minimum products</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Standard rate</li><li>Zero rate</li><li>Reduced Category rate</li><li>Advert exception</li><li>Variant exception</li><li>Taxable postage</li><li>Non-registered Seller where applicable</li><li>Valid and invalid tax codes</li><li>Multi-Seller Order</li></ul><h3>Verify</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Applied item and postage rates</li><li>Commission and Merchant Fee tax</li><li>Withholding</li><li>Customer Invoice</li><li>Refund and credit note</li><li>Seller Remittance</li><li>Reporting and accounting output</li></ul><h3>Investigate discrepancies</h3><ol><li>Platform tax model</li><li>Order submission time</li><li>Default and Item rates</li><li>Category hierarchy</li><li>Advert and Variant values</li><li>Blank versus zero</li><li>Seller registration status</li><li>Integration-supplied tax</li><li>Tax code and external response</li><li>Withholding and refund activity</li></ol><h3>Change control</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Finance and tax approval</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Impact assessment</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Sandbox testing</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Production change</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Audit Log review</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>New Order validation</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Evidence retention</strong></div></div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4627441353741-Default-Tax-Settings-Configuration\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Default Tax Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/6624429993741-Tax-Rate-Calculations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tax Rate Calculations</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4422008724365-Witholding-Tax-From-Remittances\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Withholding Tax From Remittances</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360060520811-Selling-as-a-business-not-registered-for-GST-sales-tax\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Selling as a business not registered for GST</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/6173973897613-Tax-Code-Validation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tax Code Validation</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["merchant-fees","Merchant Fees and Charges"],["remittances","Remittances"],["product-ingestion","Product Ingestion Methods"]]},"payments":{"summary":"Understand how customer payment is processed through the Operator storefront and payment provider, how Marketplacer receives the Order and payment information, and how Seller payout differs with and without MPay.","audience":["Finance","Payments","Marketplace operations","Technology and integrations","Ecommerce","Customer service","Risk and fraud"],"sections":{"Understanding the Payment Architecture":"\n<p>Marketplace payments involve separate financial events:</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Event</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer payment</td><td>Collect or authorise the amount at checkout</td></tr><tr><td>Order and Seller Invoices</td><td>Record the marketplace transaction and Seller obligations</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance calculation</td><td>Determine the net amount owed to each Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Seller payout</td><td>Transfer eligible funds</td></tr><tr><td>Customer refund</td><td>Return approved funds through the payment provider</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>The customer-facing ecommerce platform and its payment gateway or payment service provider manage checkout. Marketplacer receives the Order and relevant payment information, then tracks fulfilment and calculates Seller Remittances.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>MPay is optional.</strong> Operators that do not use MPay complete Seller fund transfers through their own finance, bank, accounting or payout process.</div>\n","Customer Payment Collection":"\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Customer checks out on the Operator storefront</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>The Operator payment provider accepts, authorises or captures the transaction</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>The ecommerce platform creates the Marketplacer Order</strong></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Marketplacer creates the Seller Invoices</strong></div></div></div>\n<p>Seller Invoices generally enter Marketplacer after the customer payment has been accepted according to the approved payment architecture. Depending on the implementation, the transaction may already be settled or may be authorised for later settlement.</p>\n<p>Preserve payment reference, method, currency, Order total, Line Item values, postage, discounts and tax so reconciliation can trace the storefront payment to the Marketplacer Order.</p>\n<h3>Failure controls</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Detect payment success with failed Order creation</li><li>Retry safely without duplicate Orders or charges</li><li>Prevent Seller fulfilment where payment is not approved</li><li>Void or refund unrecoverable transactions</li><li>Alert the responsible operations and technology teams</li></ul>\n","Configuring Payment Methods":"<p><code>Configuration &gt; Payment Methods</code></p><p>Use this area where the implementation requires Marketplacer payment methods for ecommerce or Seller billing.</p><h3>Create a method</h3><ol><li>Select New Method.</li><li>Choose the purpose, E-commerce or Billing.</li><li>Select the method and provider.</li><li>Save.</li><li>Open the provider and add the required credentials.</li><li>Test in Sandbox and complete controlled Production validation.</li></ol><h3>Credentials</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use approved secret storage</li><li>Restrict access</li><li>Separate Sandbox and Production accounts</li><li>Rotate credentials through change control</li><li>Avoid placing secrets in shared documents or screenshots</li></ul><p>Configure provider-specific Merchant Fees where payment-processing costs differ by gateway.</p>","Connected Checkout and Payment Data":"<p>In a connected marketplace, the ecommerce platform usually owns cart, checkout, customer authentication, payment selection, authorisation, capture and customer messaging. Marketplacer receives the Order and the data required for Seller fulfilment and marketplace finance.</p><p><code>Operator API: orderCreate</code></p><h3>Preserve</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Variant and quantity</li><li>Price and discount</li><li>Postage and tax</li><li>Customer and addresses</li><li>Stable payment reference</li><li>Payment source</li><li>External Order identifiers</li><li>Currency</li></ul><h3>Reconcile the value</h3><p><code>Items + postage + checkout charges - discounts + applicable tax = Customer payment total</code></p><p>Use stable references and idempotent retry controls to prevent duplicate Order creation, duplicate capture and duplicate refunds.</p><p>Decide when a Seller can see the Order. Fraud or payment-review Orders should remain outside normal fulfilment until approved.</p>","MPay and Automated Seller Payouts":"\n<p>MPay is Marketplacer's integrated Seller payout solution, provided with Airwallex. It supports payout onboarding, verification, fund allocation, financial adjustments, reconciliation and Seller payout.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Without MPay</th><th>With MPay</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer checkout</td><td>Operator storefront and payment provider</td><td>Operator storefront and payment provider</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance calculation</td><td>Marketplacer</td><td>Marketplacer</td></tr><tr><td>Actual Seller payout</td><td>Operator finance or payout process</td><td>Integrated MPay payout workflow</td></tr><tr><td>KYC and AML for payout</td><td>Operator-managed process</td><td>MPay onboarding workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Reconciliation</td><td>Operator-managed</td><td>Integrated MPay reporting and reconciliation</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>MPay does not move the customer checkout into the Operator Portal. The customer still pays through the customer-facing storefront.</p>\n","Refunds, Fraud and Chargebacks":"<p>A Refund Request controls the marketplace workflow and Seller financial adjustment. The customer's money must also be returned through the payment provider or approved payment process.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Refund approved</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Marketplacer adjustments reviewed</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Customer payment refund submitted</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Gateway result confirmed</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Refund Request finalised</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Remittance and reconciliation checked</strong></div></div><h3>Store the reference chain</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Original payment reference</li><li>Refund reference</li><li>Order and Invoice</li><li>Refund Request</li><li>Line Items and amount</li><li>Payment-provider status and time</li></ul><h3>Fraud and chargebacks</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Define the fraud-scoring system and review owner</li><li>Hold Orders from Sellers until approved</li><li>Connect chargebacks to delivery, refund and Seller evidence</li><li>Allocate financial responsibility according to policy and agreement</li><li>Record Seller recovery through the financial workflow</li></ul>","Payment Reporting and Reconciliation":"<p><code>Reporting &gt; Payment Events</code></p><p>Compare payment events with ecommerce Orders, Marketplacer Orders, Refund Requests, payment-provider records and bank settlements.</p><p><code>Reporting &gt; MPay Reporting</code></p><p>Where MPay is enabled, review matched deposits, pending reconciliations and errors.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Exception</th><th>Checks</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Unmatched payment reference</td><td>PSP transaction, ecommerce Order, Marketplacer Order, failed synchronisation</td></tr><tr><td>Amount mismatch</td><td>Tax, discount, postage, currency, partial refund, payload</td></tr><tr><td>Deposit discrepancy</td><td>PSP and intermediary fees, missing transactions, declared amount</td></tr><tr><td>Missing funds</td><td>Settlement timing, bank processing, deposit reference</td></tr><tr><td>Orphaned deposit</td><td>Manual transfer or missing reconciliation request</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Daily review</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Payment successes and failures</li><li>Marketplacer Order count</li><li>Failed Order creation</li><li>Duplicate references</li><li>Refunds created and completed</li><li>PSP settlement</li><li>MPay reconciliation exceptions</li></ul>","Testing and Ongoing Governance":"<h3>Payment test plan</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Successful and declined payment</li><li>Timeout</li><li>Payment without Order</li><li>Order without payment</li><li>Duplicate request</li><li>Multi-Seller Order</li><li>Postage and promotion</li><li>Mixed tender</li><li>Fraud review</li><li>Full and partial refund</li><li>Refund after payout</li><li>Chargeback</li><li>Deposit reconciliation</li><li>Seller payout</li></ul><h3>Production readiness</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Merchant of record confirmed</li><li>Customer payment and Seller payout owners confirmed</li><li>Credentials and webhooks secured</li><li>Order reference and duplicate protection tested</li><li>Refund and chargeback processes documented</li><li>Daily and month-end reconciliation assigned</li></ul><h3>Change control</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Approve architecture or provider change</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Configure and test in Sandbox</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Apply Production change</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Run a controlled live transaction</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Validate settlement and refund</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Complete operational handover</strong></div></div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052718492-Configuring-your-marketplace-payment-options\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure marketplace payment options</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580327625613-Introduction-to-MPay-for-Operators\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Introduction to MPay for Operators</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41579730763021-MPay-onboarding-and-account-setup-for-Operators\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MPay onboarding and account setup for Operators</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41579733838477-MPay-financial-flow-and-reporting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MPay financial flow and reporting</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/44537289358733-Understanding-deposit-reconciliation-and-error-management\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Deposit reconciliation and error management</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/reference/mutations/ordercreate/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator API orderCreate</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["remittances","Remittances"],["integration-architecture","Integration Architecture"],["refund-integrations","Refund Integrations"]]},"remittances":{"summary":"Configure when completed Seller Invoices become eligible for Remittance, distinguish payout approval, delay and schedule, and reconcile generated Remittance Advices with the actual Seller payout process.","audience":["Finance","Marketplace operations","Seller management","Commercial","Payments","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Remittances":"\n<p>A Remittance is Marketplacer's calculation of the net amount owed to a Seller for eligible marketplace activity.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Term</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer payment</td><td>Money accepted through the Operator storefront and payment provider</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Invoice</td><td>The Seller-specific portion of the Order</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance</td><td>Calculated net amount owed to the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Advice</td><td>Record explaining the processed amount</td></tr><tr><td>Payout</td><td>Actual transfer of funds to the Seller</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>A processed Remittance Advice does not by itself prove that the Seller received funds. Confirm the MPay, bank or payout-provider transaction separately.</p>\n","Remittance Eligibility and Payout Cycle":"\n<p>Marketplacer evaluates Seller activity during the Remittance process.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Is the Seller Invoice complete?</strong><p>Every Line Item on that Seller Invoice is dispatched or cancelled.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Has the Operator approved the payout for release?</strong><p>Manually or through Automatically approve payouts.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Has the remittance delay passed?</strong><p>The earliest eligibility date has been reached.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Has the Seller's scheduled Remittance cycle arrived?</strong><p>Daily, weekly, monthly or the configured schedule.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Is the net Seller position positive?</strong><p>Eligible sales, refunds and adjustments are combined.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Remittance Advice is generated</strong></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Partial fulfilment does not complete the Seller Invoice.</strong> One outstanding Line Item or quantity keeps that Invoice incomplete. Another Seller Invoice in the same Order can complete independently.</div>\n","Configuring Delay and Schedule":"\n<p>The remittance delay and Remittance schedule control different parts of payout timing.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Question answered</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Remittance delay</td><td>How long after Seller Invoice completion must the amount wait before it can become eligible?</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance schedule</td><td>On which recurring cycle does Marketplacer process eligible Seller activity?</td></tr><tr><td>Payout approval</td><td>Has the Operator permitted the amount to progress?</td></tr><tr><td>Net-positive check</td><td>Is the Seller owed a positive amount after refunds and adjustments?</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Configure marketplace defaults through <code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings</code>. Configure approved Seller-specific overrides through <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Remittance Details</code>.</p>\n<h3>Example</h3><p>A Seller Invoice completes on Monday. The Seller has a seven-day delay and a weekly Friday schedule. The delay passes the following Monday, so the first applicable scheduled cycle is Friday. If payout approval is still outstanding on that Friday, the Invoice waits for a later eligible cycle.</p>\n","Approving Payouts":"\n<p>Use <code>Orders &gt; Payouts to approve</code> for manual approval. The platform action may be labelled <strong>Release payment</strong>, but the business decision is approval for the Seller Invoice to continue through Remittance processing.</p>\n<p>Use <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Remittance Details &gt; Automatically approve payouts</code> where the approved operating model removes the manual review step.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Approval is not the fund transfer.</strong> It allows the Invoice to progress. The Seller is paid later through MPay or the Operator's own payout process.</div>\n","Calculating the Seller Remittance":"<h3>Commission Seller</h3><p><code>Eligible item and postage value - commission - Merchant Fees - withheld tax - refunds and adjustments = Net Remittance</code></p><h3>Wholesale Seller</h3><p><code>Eligible Wholesale Price + Seller-owned postage - Merchant Fees - withheld tax - refunds and adjustments = Net Remittance</code></p><p>Each Seller in a multi-Seller Order is evaluated independently using its own commercial terms, tax, delay and schedule.</p><h3>Validate</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Item price and quantity</li><li>Postage</li><li>Commission Package or Wholesale Price</li><li>Merchant Fees</li><li>Promotion funding</li><li>Item and postage tax</li><li>Refunds and amendments</li><li>Net Remittance amount</li></ul><p>Finance should be able to trace every amount from the customer transaction through the Seller Invoice and Remittance Advice.</p>","Refunds, Negative Balances and Recovery":"<h3>Refund before Remittance</h3><p>The completed Refund Request reduces the eligible Seller amount before payout.</p><h3>Refund after payout</h3><p>The Seller-funded amount becomes a Remittance to reclaim and is applied against later eligible activity.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Example position</th><th>Amount</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>New eligible sales</td><td>$100</td></tr><tr><td>Refund recovery</td><td>-$140</td></tr><tr><td>Combined position</td><td>-$40</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance generated</td><td>No</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>After later eligible sales make the combined position positive, the Seller can progress through the remaining eligibility checks.</p><h3>Monitor</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Post-payout refunds</li><li>Negative balances</li><li>Sellers with no new activity</li><li>Large recoveries</li><li>Closed or departing Sellers</li><li>Seller disputes</li></ul><p>Complete all cancellations and Refund Requests promptly so the nightly run evaluates the correct financial position.</p>","Remittance Advices, Reporting and Payout Methods":"\n<p>After all eligibility checks pass, Marketplacer generates the Remittance Advice.</p>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Without MPay</h3><p>Remittance data is made available through the configured CSV, API, accounting or finance workflow. The Operator completes the actual Seller fund transfer.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>With MPay</h3><p>The eligible amount proceeds through the integrated MPay payout and reconciliation workflow.</p></article></div>\n<p>Use <code>Reporting &gt; Remittances</code> to review processed and unprocessed activity, included Seller Invoices, adjustments and pending reasons. Match every Advice ID, amount, payment reference, payment date and payout result.</p>\n","Testing and Ongoing Finance Operations":"<h3>Minimum tests</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Commission and wholesale Seller</li><li>Default and custom delay</li><li>Daily, weekly or monthly schedule</li><li>Manual and automatic approval</li><li>Single and multiple Seller Invoices</li><li>Merchant Fees and tax withholding</li><li>Refund before and after payout</li><li>Negative balance</li><li>Missing payment details</li><li>Payout failure</li></ul><h3>Daily review</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Orders &gt; Payouts to approve</li><li>Undispatched Invoices</li><li>Unprocessed Remittances and pending reasons</li><li>Missing payment details</li><li>Failed payouts</li><li>Refund recoveries</li><li>Seller enquiries</li><li>MPay errors where applicable</li></ul><h3>Investigate a missing Remittance</h3><ol><li>Confirm Invoice completion.</li><li>Check manual release or automatic approval.</li><li>Check delay and schedule.</li><li>Check Seller payment details and provider status.</li><li>Review combined balance and refund activity.</li><li>Review processed and unprocessed reporting.</li><li>Confirm payout status and payment reference.</li></ol><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16214109276045-Understanding-remittance-advices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Understanding remittance advices</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040328092-Releasing-remittances\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Releasing remittances</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16214118514189-View-remittance-summary-as-an-operator-implementation-2-0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View remittance summary as an Operator</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038673291-Calculating-remittance-on-orders\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Calculating remittance on Orders</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/45368727546637-Remittance-reporting-with-MPay-automated-payouts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Remittance reporting with MPay</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["payments","Payments"],["finance-reporting","Finance Operations and Reporting"],["refund-financial-adjustments","Refund Financial Adjustments"]]},"finance-reporting":{"summary":"Establish the daily, weekly and month-end processes used to reconcile marketplace sales, Seller Invoices, refunds, fees, tax, Remittances and payouts. Connect Marketplacer records with payment-provider, accounting, bank and analytical data.","audience":["Finance","Marketplace operations","Payments","Seller management","Commercial","Tax","Technology and data"],"sections":{"Understanding Finance Operations":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Customer payment</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Marketplacer Order</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Seller Invoices and Line Items</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Commission or Wholesale Price</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Fees, tax, refunds and amendments</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Remittance</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Payout</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><strong>Accounting and bank reconciliation</strong></div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Record</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Order</td><td>Customer purchase</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Invoice</td><td>Seller portion of the Order</td></tr><tr><td>Line Item</td><td>Purchased Variant and financial values</td></tr><tr><td>Refund Request</td><td>Cancellation or return workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice Amendment</td><td>Approved financial adjustment</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Invoice</td><td>Commission and Seller charges</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Advice</td><td>Net Seller amount processed</td></tr><tr><td>Payout record</td><td>Movement of money</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>One customer Order can create several Seller Invoices. Reconcile at both Order and Invoice level and define the source of truth for customer payment, marketplace calculation, payout and general ledger.</p><h3>Assign ownership</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Payment reconciliation</li><li>Refund reconciliation</li><li>Commission and wholesale validation</li><li>Tax</li><li>Remittance approval</li><li>Seller payout</li><li>Bank reconciliation</li><li>Seller finance enquiries</li><li>Month-end close</li><li>Financial change control</li></ul>","Finance Operating Rhythm":"<h3>Daily</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Payment captured without Order and Order without payment</li><li>Duplicate or mismatched references</li><li>Undispatched Seller Invoices</li><li>Orders &gt; Payouts to approve</li><li>Refunds approved but not paid or finalised</li><li>New Remittance Advices and unprocessed reasons</li><li>Negative balances and failed payouts</li><li>MPay exceptions</li></ul><h3>Nightly Remittance run</h3><p>Marketplacer evaluates Seller activity overnight. Each morning, review newly processed Remittance Advices, pending reasons, missing payment details, negative positions and payout errors. Activity that does not qualify is checked again during a later nightly run.</p><h3>Weekly</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Sales and completed Seller Invoices</li><li>Commission, wholesale margin and Merchant Fees</li><li>Refund and cancellation value</li><li>Tax collected and withheld</li><li>Processed and unprocessed Remittances</li><li>Seller payouts and aged exceptions</li><li>Seller-level operational trends</li></ul><h3>Monthly</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Customer payments</li><li>Sales</li><li>Refunds and chargebacks</li><li>Operator earnings</li><li>Tax</li><li>Remittances</li><li>Seller payouts</li><li>Accounting and bank balances</li></ul>","All Sales and Transaction-Level Review":"<p><code>Orders &gt; All Sales</code></p><p>Use All Sales to investigate Orders, Seller Invoices and Line Items. Filters can include Order and Invoice number, status, dates, Seller, product, payment failure and Remittance status.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Created date</td><td>When the record entered Marketplacer</td></tr><tr><td>Paid date</td><td>When associated payment was recorded</td></tr><tr><td>Completed date</td><td>When the Seller Invoice completed</td></tr><tr><td>Remit after</td><td>Earliest eligibility after delay</td></tr><tr><td>Remitted date</td><td>When included in a processed Remittance</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Select the table columns before exporting because the export reflects the visible fields.</p><h3>Standard investigation</h3><ol><li>Search the Invoice.</li><li>Review every Line Item and fulfilment status.</li><li>Confirm item, postage and tax.</li><li>Confirm Commission Package or Wholesale Price.</li><li>Review Merchant Fees, promotions and refunds.</li><li>Review Remittance and payout reference.</li><li>Compare payment-provider and accounting records.</li></ol><h3>Period-end snapshots</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Record filters, date basis and visible columns</li><li>Record extraction timestamp and time zone</li><li>Store the export in a controlled Finance location</li><li>Retain later adjustments separately</li><li>Use a data warehouse for repeatable point-in-time reporting</li></ul>","Financial Reports and Documents":"<p>Depending on configuration and permissions, Finance may use:</p><p><code>Reporting &gt; Sales Reports | Remittances | Payment Events | MPay Reporting | Audit Logs</code></p><h3>Documents</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Tax Invoice</li><li>Commission Invoice</li><li>Seller credit note</li><li>Commission credit note</li><li>Remittance PDF</li><li>Additional Charges Invoice</li></ul><p>Confirm legal entity, registration number, Seller, Order and Invoice references, item values, postage, tax, commission, Merchant Fees, refunds, total and currency.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Question</th><th>Starting point</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Why is this Seller Invoice amount different?</td><td>Orders &gt; All Sales</td></tr><tr><td>What commission was charged?</td><td>All Sales and Commission Invoice</td></tr><tr><td>Why has the Seller not been paid?</td><td>Unprocessed Remittances</td></tr><tr><td>What was included in the payout?</td><td>Remittance Advice</td></tr><tr><td>Was money transferred?</td><td>MPay, payout provider or bank</td></tr><tr><td>Who changed a Finance setting?</td><td>Audit Logs</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use Audit Logs and the configuration register to connect financial-setting changes with approvals and first affected transactions.</p>","Remittance and Payout Reconciliation":"<p><code>Reporting &gt; Remittances</code></p><h3>Processed advice review</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Advice ID and date</li><li>Seller and net amount</li><li>Included Invoices and amendments</li><li>Refund recoveries</li><li>Payment method and reference</li><li>Payout and bank status</li></ul><h3>Unprocessed review</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Incomplete Seller Invoice</li><li>Payment not released</li><li>Delay not passed</li><li>Schedule not reached</li><li>Missing payment details</li><li>Negative balance</li><li>Provider status issue</li><li>Processing error</li></ul><h3>Match the payout</h3><p><code>Advice ID + Seller + Net amount + Payment reference + Payment date + Provider or bank result = Reconciled payout</code></p><p>Monitor post-payout refund recovery, Sellers with no future sales and balances that need direct collection before Seller closure.</p>","Payment and MPay Reconciliation":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Payment-provider transaction</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Ecommerce Order</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Marketplacer Order</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Seller Invoices</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Refunds</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Remittance Advices</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Seller and Operator payouts</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><strong>Bank activity</strong></div></div><h3>Payment Events</h3><p><code>Reporting &gt; Payment Events</code></p><p>Investigate payment attempts, failures, provider responses, references and timestamps.</p><h3>MPay Reporting</h3><p><code>Reporting &gt; MPay Reporting</code></p><p>Review matched deposits, pending reconciliation, holding-account activity and payout status. Use the MPay payment ID when investigating a payout or raising a Support request.</p><h3>Segregation of duties</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Separate bank-detail maintenance from payout approval</li><li>Independently review payment files</li><li>Use delegated bank authorisation</li><li>Reconcile after payment</li><li>Monitor access and changes</li></ul>","Data Exports and Advanced Analytics":"<p>Use Operator Portal reports for current operational investigation and standard exports. Use APIs, webhooks or Snowflake Data Sharing for automated reconciliation, historical analysis and custom dashboards.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Best suited to</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Portal reports</td><td>Daily operations, Seller queries and standard close evidence</td></tr><tr><td>APIs and webhooks</td><td>Automated pipelines and near-real-time monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Snowflake Data Sharing</td><td>Historical, cross-domain and modelled analysis</td></tr><tr><td>BI tools</td><td>Marketplace-specific dashboards and controls</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Define every metric</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Name and business definition</li><li>Grain</li><li>Date basis and time zone</li><li>Included statuses</li><li>Refund and tax treatment</li><li>Currency</li><li>Seller scope</li><li>Source table or report</li><li>Owner</li></ul><h3>Protect data</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Report and export permissions</li><li>PII access</li><li>API and Snowflake roles</li><li>Controlled storage</li><li>Retention policy</li><li>Seller bank and customer information</li></ul>","Month-End Close and Governance":"<h3>Month-end sequence</h3><ol><li>Confirm period, time zone, date basis and extraction time.</li><li>Reconcile PSP transactions to ecommerce and Marketplacer Orders.</li><li>Reconcile sales, Seller Invoices, postage, promotions and tax.</li><li>Reconcile commission, wholesale margin and Merchant Fees.</li><li>Reconcile refunds, credit notes and chargebacks.</li><li>Reconcile processed and unprocessed Remittances.</li><li>Match payouts to provider and bank activity.</li><li>Review suspense, negative balances and aged exceptions.</li><li>Complete Finance sign-off and retain evidence.</li></ol><h3>Finance controls</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Role-based access</li><li>Approval of Finance Settings and Seller exceptions</li><li>Controlled package, cost, fee, tax and schedule changes</li><li>Monitoring of Seller bank-detail changes</li><li>Independent payout review and release</li><li>Standard report definitions</li><li>Period-end snapshots and evidence</li></ul><h3>Discrepancy investigation</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Environment and Order</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Seller Invoice and Line Items</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Prices, postage and tax</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Commission or Wholesale Price</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Fees, promotions and refunds</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Remittance Advice</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Payout reference and provider status</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><strong>Bank and accounting entry</strong></div></div><p>Include the environment, Seller, Order, Invoice, Line Item, Refund Request, Remittance Advice, payment ID, expected and actual values, dates, report filters and troubleshooting in a Support request.</p><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14369804027661-Access-to-data-for-Analysis\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Access to data for Analysis</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16214109276045-Understanding-remittance-advices\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Understanding remittance advices</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/45368727546637-Remittance-reporting-with-MPay-automated-payouts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Remittance reporting with MPay</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator user role permissions</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["remittances","Remittances"],["sales-reporting","Sales Reporting"],["weekly-monthly-operations","Weekly and Monthly Operations"]]}};
